{
  "stem": "22586.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] took us three days until we arrived what we now know is Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We didn't know where we were when we arrived.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We just know that finally they opened the doors.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "During the three days that we traveled, there was no food, except what we took with us from camp.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we didn't have much then.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So some of the people even died in the cars.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They were not removed for the three days.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "There were no-- there was no place to sit, so we're just standing there for the three days.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And after three days, we arrived in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The doors were opened.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And we saw people in [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] some kind of clothing.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We didn't know what-- who they were.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But they were wearing gray and blue striped-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I can't call it uniforms, but clothes.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And apparently they were inmates from Auschwitz who were assigned to work, to have these people get out of the cars and line-- line them up.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] And they put men to one side and women went to the other side.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And then I remember my oldest sister saying that since my mother was with my younger brother, that she's going to go with my mother to help her take care of my brother, not knowing that that group was actually destined to go to the gas chamber.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 10 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I was with my sister Elizabeth in a different group.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
